## wakeup-source

**Value type:** `<empty>`

Presence of this property indicates the device can be used as a wakeup source, allowing it to wake the system from a suspended state. The presence of the property alone (no value) is sufficient.

This property replaces the deprecated `gpio-key,wakeup` property used in older devicetrees.

```dts
/* arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8550-qrd.dts */
key-vol-down {
    linux,code = <KEY_VOLUMEDOWN>;
    wakeup-source;
};
```
